-- Standard Chartered Global Personal Banking Head Khoo to Leave
-- B y   S a n a t   V a l l i k a p p e n   a n d   J o y c e   K o h
-- 2013-07-17T07:32:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-17/standard-chartered-global-personal-banking-head-khoo-to-leave.html
Standard Chartered  Plc said that
Dennis Khoo, its global head of personal and preferred banking
in  Singapore , is leaving after 12 years at the U.K. bank.  Khoo will depart on July 19 to “pursue other interests,”
Tan Hsueh Mei, a spokeswoman for Standard Chartered in
Singapore, said in an e-mailed response to queries.  Before taking his current position, Khoo was head of
Singapore consumer banking, Tan said. Khoo declined to comment
when reached by mobile phone today.  To contact the reporters on this story:
